In a decision that will almost certainly lead to the first work stoppage in National Basketball Association history, the league announced the cancellation of all 114 preseason games.
While the decision had been expected for 10 days, it nonetheless sent a strong signal that the owners and players will probably be willing to cancel at least part of the regular season in order to settle their labor dispute.
In a critical ruling for the North American National Basketball Association and the players' union, arbitrator John Feerick decides whether more than 200 players with guaranteed contracts should be paid during the lockout.
